On April 12th 2017, my Aunt Sheila’s body was found in the Hudson River. After many meetings with the New York Police Department, the Chief Medical Examiner, and the Manhattan District Attorney’s office her death has continued to be ruled a suicide. The information and files that we have received from them have been inconclusive and do not support suicide as a cause of death. Our family never believed she would take her own life when she was at the peak of her legal career and we feel that foul play was involved in her death. It has been three years and we have yet to receive any authentic answers, which is especially concerning based on her being the first African American woman to serve on New York’s highest Court of Appeals. This is why we have decided to go public at this time and demand justice for Sheila Abdus-Salaam. Losing her tragically in this way has caused a lot of pain to us, and not receiving the reasonable information from any thorough investigative work has been very frustrating. My aunt Sheila should still be here fighting for justice for the citizens of New York and now she deserves justice. Her life mattered so much to not only her family, friends and colleagues but also to the world! We would really appreciate any information from the public that will assist in the re-opening and further investigation into her case. There is also a petition that I created that you can sign in my bio. We would really appreciate your help and support. Please feel free to share and tag as many people as possible in the post on my page and share and sign the petition. We want to get as many to as many people as we can. If you have any information please reach out to me directly. WE DEMAND ANSWERS & JUSTICE! 🙏🏾 #SheilaAbdusSalaam #JusticeforSheilaAbdusSalaam

¿Cuáles son sus predicciones para el futuro próximo, y para Rusia y para Europa. El mundo parece un poco loco.?
- Sí, muy enojado. Tengo 73 años y he visto mucho. No puedo guardar silencio por más tiempo, no puedo dormir, no puedo caminar por las calles de brazos cruzados y ver pasear a los jóvenes que no tienen idea de lo que realmente está pasando en el país y en el mundo. Estoy harto de ver televisión, leer el periódico. En todas partes sarta de mentiras. Estaba insoportablemente doloroso para la generación más joven, tanto es así que el corazón está a punto de detenerse. Nadie sabe la verdad. Mundial analiza las elecciones en los Estados Unidos, los conflictos en Turquía y otros países, en Rusia, aunque sus opciones no discuten, por lo general, todos los interesados en el más barato que ir a descansar. Sin embargo, esta elección es el último de todos. Para todos, de nuevo. No habrá más de este mundo, que veremos este verano. Todo cambiará pronto de forma espectacular.
La gente muchas décadas dirigidos por la nariz. Usted vive en una realidad diferente. La humanidad está al borde de la muerte.
